## New Features ##

### [???] Added new `get_current_timestring` lua function
This function returns a string representation of the time in YYYY-MM-DD
HH:MM:SS format This format has the advantage that ordering by time is the same
as ordering the strings lexicographically.

Example usage is:

~~~
local timestr = get_current_timestring()
if timestr < "2013-01-01 00:00:00" then 
  print("Its still 2012")
end
~~~


